cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of distributed formation stabilization of multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also presents an angle rigidity theory to study the uniqueness of planar frameworks, which is related to Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a distributed control law for agents, which is related to Dynamical Systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of formation stabilization, which is related to Graph Theory (cs.GR).
